.TH "s5p_hash_copy_sgs" 9 "s5p_hash_copy_sgs" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
s5p_hash_copy_sgs \- copy request's bytes into new buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" s5p_hash_copy_sgs
.BI "(struct s5p_hash_reqctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *sg "  ","
.BI "unsigned int new_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
request context
.IP "sg" 12
source scatterlist request
.IP "new_len" 12
number of bytes to process from sg
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate new buffer, copy data for HASH into it. If there was xmit_buf
filled, copy it first, then copy data from sg into it. Prepare one sgl[0]
with allocated buffer.

Set bit in dd->hash_flag so we can free it after irq ends processing.
